To create a spfile from pfile
==============================
create spfile='+DATA_1' from pfile='/u01/app/oracle/product/12.2.0.1/db_1/dbs/compEn3.ora';

It will automatically created into respective spfile directory inside the ASM

To create a pfile from spfile
==============================
create pfile from spfile

It will create a default naming pfile inside the dbs directory.
or else you can specify the directory yourself

create pfile='/home/oracle/my.ora' from spfile


There are lot more options available.... just to show some basic but some important ones....
